      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">8.405-5</ph> Small business.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d461e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d469e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   Although the preference programs
of part <xref href="FAR-i1101928.dita#i1101928"
                        base="i1101928"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19</xref> are not mandatory in
this subpart, in accordance with section 1331 of Public Law 111-240
(<xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref "> 15 U.S.C. 644</xref>(r))-</p>
               <ol id="d461e29" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d469e33" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         Ordering
activity contracting officers may, at their discretion-</p>
                     <ol id="d461e39" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d469e43" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Set
aside orders for any of the small business concerns identified in <xref href="FAR-i1101771.dita#i1101771"
                                    base="i1101771"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3); and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d469e55" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Set aside
BPAs for any of the small business concerns identified in <xref href="FAR-i1101771.dita#i1101771"
                                    base="i1101771"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">19.000</xref>(a)(3).</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d469e69" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                         When setting
aside orders and BPAs-</p>
                     <ol id="d461e75" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d469e79" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               Follow the ordering procedures
for Federal Supply Schedules at 8.405-1, <xref href="FAR-i1117591.dita#i1117591"
                                    base="i1117591"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">8.405-2</xref>, and <xref href="FAR-i1117655.dita#i1117655"
                                    base="i1117655"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">8.405-3</xref>; and</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d469e94" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                              
                               The specific
small business program eligibility requirements identified in part <xref href="FAR-i1101928.dita#i1101928"
                                    base="i1101928"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">19</xref> apply.</p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d469e110" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   Orders
placed against schedule contracts may be credited toward the ordering
activityâ€™s small business goals. For purposes of reporting an order
placed with a small business schedule contractor, an ordering agency
may only take credit if the awardee meets a size standard that corresponds
to the work performed. Ordering activities should rely on the small business
representations made by schedule contractors at the contract level.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d469e119" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   Ordering
activities may consider socio-economic status when identifying contractor(s)
for consideration or competition for award of an order or BPA. At
a minimum, ordering activities should consider, if available, at
least one small business, veteran-owned small business, service
disabled veteran-owned small business, HUBZone small business, women-owned
small business, or small disadvantaged business schedule contractor(s).
GSA Advantage! and Schedules e-Library at <xref href="http://www.gsa.gov/fas"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">http://www.gsa.gov/fas</xref> contain
information on the small business representations of Schedule contractors.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d469e131" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                   For orders
exceeding the micro-purchase threshold, ordering activities should
give preference to the items of small business concerns when two
or more items at the same delivered price will satisfy the requirement.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
   </concept>
